[57.123501, "o", "kip the standard assertions and use different validation logic instead. The issue is that adding a no-path scenario would break the non-optimal finder tests since they'd try to access properties on an empty array. For the start==end case, I'm uncertain whether all finders handle it consistently, so that could also cause failures. I think the safest approach is to run the existing tests first to see what's currently working, then decide whether to add scenarios to the shared file or create a separate test file for edge cases. for optimal finders, but the non-optimal ones would crash trying to access an undefined array element. I think the safest approach is to skip adding the no-path scenario altogether and instead write a separate test specifically for it, since modifying PathTest.js directly isn't allowed. start==end in a separate focused test file. Only add the 1×1 grid scenario to PathTestScenarios.js if start==end is safe.\\n\\nActually, I need to reconsider—PathTestScenarios.js is test data, not the act"]
[57.123511, "o", "ual test files themselves. The real tests are in PathTest.js, Grid.js, and Util.js. But adding new scenarios there would still cause those existing tests to run against new inputs, which could break them if the finders don't handle those cases properly.\\n\\nFor the no-path scenario, that's definitely unsafe to add since non-optimal finders would fail on an empty array. The start==end case is trickier—if all finders return a single-element path, the existing assertions should pass, but I'd need to verify that none of them return an empty array instead.\\n\\nI'll take the pragmatic approach: add only what I'm confident won't break existing tests, and create separate test files for the riskier scenarios. My actual plan is to fix the smoothenPath variable declaration bug and then extend the utility tests with the new cases.\",\"signature\":\"EqdFClsIDBgCKkDWiAUaAVbIZ6vaEmLKW44uDdaougOuCJ/4qPB5YaO4y62yCT/+4g5PBr+IUwEcqpSr4opzvcdC+UbA9+UTAJ78MhFjbGF1ZGUtc29ubmV0LTQtNjgAEgzFYcR+t6Pjz4w0YPsaDI5us9nRNeVmMNXc5iIwbi0/OSzlGQx"]
